<p>On Monday, Samantha sat down for an interview with CNN to talk about a series of 'creepy' comments she says Trump made about her when she was 15 years old.</p>

<p>Her appearance on New Day came as Cohen's new book Disloyal: A Memoir hit bookshelves.</p>

<p>In the book, Cohen claims that in 2012 Trump whistled at his then-teen daughter as she was playing tennis, remarking 'what a piece of a**. I would love some of that.'</p>

<p>After Cohen told Trump that she was his daughter, he allegedly replied 'when did she get so hot?', and then beckoned her over to come and kiss him on the cheek.</p>

<p>Cohen's book Disloyal was released recently</p>

<p>Speaking about the encounter, Samantha said it gave her the impression that Trump was interested in 'younger women.'</p>

